# App version (`versionCode` / `versionName`)

## Goal

Each time **installable app** changes are **committed and pushed** to `main`, **`ncarouselBaseVersionName`** must increase (at least **patch**) so CI can publish tag **`v<versionName>`** and a **new** GitHub Release. **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`** must **+1** every time as well, with a matching Fastlane changelog file (see `.cursor/rules/45-changelog-fdroid.mdc` and `.cursor/rules/50-commit-push-release-automation.mdc`).

## Gradle fields

- **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`**: +1 on every release-ready push that ships app changes (monotonic for installs without `GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER`).
- **`ncarouselBaseVersionName`**: bump patch (or minor/major) so the **public version string** and **git tag** advance — required for a **new** Releases page entry.

## CI note

On **GitHub Actions**, `versionCode` can use `1000 + GITHUB_RUN_NUMBER` when that env is set; `versionName` becomes `ncarouselBaseVersionName+$run`. **Still** keep **`ncarouselLocalVersionCode`** and **`ncarouselBaseVersionName`** moving on each app publish so local builds and F-Droid-style metadata stay consistent and each release is identifiable.
